# Spec Kit — Spec-Driven Development backbone

This project uses **GitHub Spec Kit** (<https://github.github.com/spec-kit/>) as the SDD
backbone. All agents and subagents use it. Full playbook: `skills/spec-kit/SKILL.md`.

## Golden rule

If a phase has a matching `/speckit.*` command, **run that command** and treat its artifact
(`spec.md` / `plan.md` / `tasks.md` / constitution) as **canonical**. SDLC docs
(REQ/SDD/TDD/TEST, ADRs, API contracts) **supplement and reference** Spec Kit artifacts —
never contradict them.

## Command map

| Phase | Command |
|-------|---------|
| adapt / intake | `/speckit.constitution` |
| Intake / Requirements | `/speckit.specify` |
| Business grilling | `/speckit.clarify` |
| Design | `/speckit.plan` (+ `/speckit.checklist`) |
| Planning | `/speckit.tasks` → `/speckit.analyze` → `/speckit.taskstoissues` |
| Implementation | `/speckit.implement` |
| Convergence | `/speckit.converge` (loop to implement until converged) |

## Install & init

- Install: `uv tool install specify-cli --from git+https://github.com/github/spec-kit.git`
- Per repo (after `agentic-tool install --host cursor`): `specify init . --integration cursor`
- Manifest flag: `spec_kit.enabled`. Artifacts in `.specify/` and `specs/NNN-slug/`.

## Rules

- `/speckit.analyze` (and `/speckit.checklist`) run **before** the matching pipeline gate; a
  gate never passes on a red analyze.
- Feature context is keyed to the git branch (`NNN-slug`).
- If Spec Kit is unavailable, state **SPEC-KIT DEGRADED** and fall back to hand-written SDLC
  docs under the session folder, keeping the same gates.
- No secrets in spec/plan/tasks/constitution.
